title: For Sale:  POF p415 5.56 Silver AR-15
postcontent: The POF-USA rifle is somewhat revolutionary in the world of AR-15 platforms. It consists of a short-stroke, rotating-bolt, gas-piston system called C.R.O.S. (Corrosion Resistant Operating System). This system eliminates many of the standard parts required on the gas-impingement system such as the gas tube, gas key and gas rings. In addition to the C.R.O.S., DeSomma (founder of POF) implemented a two-piece Moular Railed Receiver (M.R.R.) with an oversized heat-sink barrel nut on the P415. Theses two systems  dissipate heat away from the working parts of the gun reducing the main cause for malfunctions—heat.       Everything in the photos is included in this premium AR package-  Viktor stock, Ergo grip, Bushnell red dot optic (sighted in) over a UTG riser, tactical rail mounted flashlight, 8 pMag 30rnd magazines with window, Grip-pod bipod w/ military grade steel, Troy sling and soft carrying case. This rifle has been fired less than 100 rounds. Two of the magazines will come fully loaded for you're first test fire, incase you don't have ammo.    Feel free to call instead of email if you prefer, 720-971-1407.  Matt S.

title: For Sale/Trade:  *Henry Golden Boy NIB and Henry Scope Mount
location: Palmyra near New Albany, Indiana, United States
postcontent:
I live in New Albany-- WILL TRADE- Henry Golden Boy (.22 lever action rifle) NEW IN BOX, comes with Brass Buttplate, Brass Receiver and the optional and coveted Brass Barrel-Band; also has the preferred Octagon Barrel with the gold engraving on both sides. It will also come with the Henry Model Cantilever scope mount. Henry doesn't drill and tap nor do they cut scope grooves in the brass receiver of the Golden Boy, so they make and sell their own scope mount just for this rifle. The scope mount attaches to the top of the barrel by removing the rear site and bolting scope mount to top of barrel with the included screws. It's all new, it's all Henry. I intended on putting a scope on here, that's why I ordered their scope mount. I went through some pictures of Henry Golden Boys with scopes installed and found the scope that looks great on this cowboy rifle...it looks right- so I ordered it. It will likely be here after the rifle is sold. I'll put it on something else I guess. The wood is very dark and is beautiful on this rifle. I have the regular Henry also, the "blued" .22 lever rifle and the wood on this Golden model is so much nicer. I have never had anything like this rifle; the lever action is smooth like butter, the brass gleams all over like it's made of gold...it will be hard for someone to shoot it because it is so incredible looking. It came with a velvet "sock" wrapped around the brass receiver, Henry shipped it that way. It's a piece of art. It's not cheap, but there's nothing else like it.
I've got $695.00 in it, with the scope mount... I want $600.00 for all of it, to sell it. It is a little tough to find one of these right now. Henry Manufacturing experienced a Hurricane and then a fire at the plant over the last 10 months and production halted. That has made Henry .22's a little hard to get. But either way, I drove for a 5 hour round trip to get this one. Then ordered the scope mount from Henry. All total I've spent 695.00, I need 600.00 of it back or I won't sell it. I need to sell it or at least trade it, but I won't give it away. The pictures are with the Henry scope mount installed. You can see how it sits over top the receiver without touching the receiver. It's ready for a scope. The box for the Henry mount is in the picture too. I will take the mount off if you want...and put the site back on if you like. Or leave it the way it is and give you the rear site in a ziplock. However you like. Email if you want 10 or so more pictures.
The pics don't do the brass justice...not at all. It's perfect. I'll also give you 200 rounds of ammo just in case you have none. Will trade for:
I want cash, but if you can come up with 300.00 - 350.00 in cash, I would think about trading on the rest. I would trade for anything if I liked it. If you want to JUST trade, it has to be something that I just can't say "no" to. I'll consider most anything. I bought this rifle for my wife's birthday, it's too big and heavy for her, she is small, so I went right back out and bought the regular "blued" Henry .22 just 4 days later. Which she can handle better. This one has to go, I have too much invested in .22 rifles. I originally posted this for 650.00, then reposted it for 600.00 the next day because I don't want it to take long to sell. I bought her another Henry, so now I've got 700.00 just sitting here in a box, I'd like to convert it to something else.
